[node name="Level6" type="Node3D"]
editor_description = "Room 06 — Overcharge Precision. A single wall at z=-10 splits the room; only a 2m gap in its center is open, guarded by a RotatingGate that cycles closed/open on a timer. Gear1 (near side) is reachable with a normal kick. Gear2 + Vial (far side) require timing a kick through the gate — Overcharge (hold past full charge) adds range but wobbles aim, so clearing the gap cleanly is a real risk/reward call, not just \"charge to max and go.\" GREYBOX FIRST PASS — gate cycle_duration/open_ratio and the corridor distance are unverified numbers, expect to retune both in-editor."

